STATE of Oregon, Plaintiff-Respondent,
v.
Charles Evans NAYLOR, Defendant-Appellant. A164388 Court of Appeals of Oregon. Submitted August 29, 2018.
November 28, 2018 Ernest G. Lannet, Chief Defender, Criminal Appellate Section, and Sarah Laidlaw, Deputy Public Defender, Office of Public Defense Services, filed the brief for appellant. Ellen F. Rosenblum, Attorney General, Benjamin Gutman, Solicitor General, and E. Nani Apo, Assistant Attorney General, filed the brief for respondent. Before Armstrong, Presiding Judge, and Tookey, Judge, and Sercombe, Senior Judge. PER CURIAM

Reversed. State v. Fonte , 363 Or. 327 , 422 P.3d 202 (2018).
